00:21:12.771 --> 00:21:14.771
now it's like the market for, 
like, YA 

00:21:15.820 --> 00:21:17.895
comics and kid comics and stuff 
like that has burst forward and 

00:21:17.896 --> 00:21:19.896
I think the 

00:21:21.575 --> 00:21:23.575
most prominent people doing that
are -- 

00:21:24.665 --> 00:21:27.514
like Randy feltmeyer is the apex
of all of that, and loved by 

00:21:27.515 --> 00:21:31.201
girls and boys, and that's 
encouraging, of course, and then

00:21:31.202 --> 00:21:33.202
you have other issues how 
identity 

00:21:34.668 --> 00:21:36.922
becomes a marketable thing and 
all these other things, but that

00:21:36.923 --> 00:21:38.923
has changed so 

00:21:40.427 --> 00:21:42.427
much since I started.

00:21:43.678 --> 00:21:45.678
&gt;&gt; MARTHA: And look at the 
comics pages 

00:21:47.343 --> 00:21:49.343
in newspapers and it's better 
online.

00:21:51.374 --> 00:21:53.831
&gt;&gt;  I mean, for me, you know, so
many years ago, to be the first 

00:21:53.832 --> 00:21:57.147
black woman in the mainstream 
press in the newspapers, that 

00:21:57.148 --> 00:22:02.176
was big.  But also by me being 
the first black woman in the 

00:22:02.177 --> 00:22:04.681
mainstream press in newspapers, 
I was the only one, and I 

00:22:07.743 --> 00:22:10.607
was kind of -- you think you're 
breaking the door down, so more 

00:22:10.608 --> 00:22:12.861
can come in, but you're really 
clogging the door, you know, 

00:22:12.862 --> 00:22:14.862
