00:22:29.596 --> 00:22:31.596
recognized a black woman 
cartoonist for the newspaper.

00:22:33.273 --> 00:22:35.273
The newspapers are dying, 
clearly, but it's true.

00:22:36.779 --> 00:22:38.651
So it's hard for me in my 
specific area of doing this to 

00:22:38.652 --> 00:22:41.537
see progress.  So that's a 
downer.

00:22:44.633 --> 00:22:46.462
&gt;&gt;  I think that as a result, 
like web comics have been so 

00:22:46.463 --> 00:22:48.926
embraced by women because 
there's -- you can just skip 

00:22:50.161 --> 00:22:52.161
directly to your audience, 
right?

00:22:54.046 --> 00:22:56.046
And I think that that's now, if 
you go 

00:22:58.147 --> 00:23:00.175
to the Expo here outside of -- 
in Bethesda, Maryland, you see 

00:23:00.176 --> 00:23:04.210
that gradually change, like more
women and they build their 

00:23:04.211 --> 00:23:06.649
audience -- clearly there is an 
appetite for it, and for 

00:23:07.042 --> 00:23:09.042
racialized women as well.

00:23:10.940 --> 00:23:13.621
And so you don't have to 
necessarily go through these 

00:23:13.622 --> 00:23:15.622
mainstream channels to, like, 
get your work out, and then 

00:23:17.549 --> 00:23:18.355
there's a reverse thing of, 
like, now the mainstream wants 

00:23:18.356 --> 00:23:20.356
that thing.

00:23:22.871 --> 00:23:25.950
It's like a turn-around.
&gt;&gt; MARTHA: Great.  Good point.

00:23:29.219 --> 00:23:31.219
And this leads me to another 
question.

00:23:33.929 --> 00:23:35.786
Could you comment on the impact 
of social media on work in both 

00:23:35.787 --> 00:23:37.787
fields?

00:23:39.300 --> 00:23:42.366
What do you think about that?
&gt;&gt;  I think about --

00:23:43.178 --> 00:23:46.320
&gt;&gt;  Positive and negative.
&gt;&gt;  Me?

00:23:47.776 --> 00:23:49.776
&gt;&gt;  Yes, all three of you.  I 
would love to hear what...

00:23:52.262 --> 00:23:54.262
&gt;&gt;  You know, social media is a 
strange bird.

00:23:56.154 --> 00:23:57.986
And I am older, so it's even 
stranger to me, because it's 

00:23:57.987 --> 00:24:01.022
new.  So it's not all good, but 
there are some good points.

00:24:04.687 --> 00:24:06.687
It does help create communities 
that 

00:24:07.978 --> 00:24:10.243
are supportive, you know, you 
can -- I can -- every once in a 

00:24:10.244 --> 00:24:14.585
while I can feel compelled to do
a strip and I can put it on my 

00:24:14.586 --> 00:24:16.586
Facebook page.  I actually have 
one.

00:24:19.897 --> 00:24:21.897
And I can get such a positive 
response.

00:24:22.966 --> 00:24:26.663
Like, do it again, Barbara! We 
need to hear these girls.  Let's

00:24:26.664 --> 00:24:28.700
